history.text: Hello
Hi, have you seen the movie?
No, I have not.  Have you?
I have. it was pretty good. I didn't realize at the time it was based on a true story
What's the story about?

Alan Turing, he invented a machine
 to break codes during, i think WW2
Oh really?  I only recognize Kiera Knightley's name on the cast list.  Is the rest of the cast good?
Benedict Cumberbatch was very good in it. I don't recognize any of the others
I've heard of him, but I don't think I've ever seen a movie he's in.  It seems like this is a primarily UK movie.
Yeah I think it was produced in Europe but it did very well here, won some awards even.
The critical response looks like it's a movie everyone should see.  I'm just not really a fan of biopics.
So he was gay, too. which was taboo at the time. I didn't feel that added much to the story though.
Like most movies "based" on true stories. They embellish enough to make it exciting and enjoyable.
I've never even heard of the person the movie is about.  It's interesting that they talked about him being gay.  I hope it wasn't just to sell movie tickets.
Most biopics are definitely just "based on a true story" but painted as the real thing.
I don't recall it being talked about at all in marketing, it was just revealed along the way in the movie
Oh that's interesting!  I think gay people should be represented in movies more.  This is great!

I suppose the more I think about it, I liked this biopic because the topic was about war history, which interests me.  Most other biopics would be fairly boring if they weren't in a genre that interested me.

Homosexuality is definitely
 portrayed much more positively on TV today than it ever had in the past. And that is great.
Ahh, I see.  I'm not really into war stories either.  I'm more of a horror or comedy person myself.
And they are being given more awards at the awards shows, too.  I think minorities are getting more and more acknowledgement in the movie industry.
Wow, this movie came out in 2014, it seems a lot longer ago that I saw it. Reading some of the key scenes and i completely forgot some of it.
I forget the dates movies come out all the time!   In a way it seems so long ago, but in another way it seems like yesterday!
What's really crazy is that Harry Potter is over 20 years old! Unreal.
I feel so old, I read those books when they came out
WHOA!  It seems like only yesterday I was reading those books and and waiting for the movies to come out.  I feel old, too!
I'm feeling like I don't quite understand this task. Were we supposed to talk about this movie more?
Yeah, we probably got off track a bit.
Quite alright, it appears we're done, nice chatting with you
Nice chatting with you, too!

uid1response.feedback: We did go off track a little bit talking about movies.
